description: Core standards for Node-RED Business Central plugin work
alwaysApply: true
---

# Core Standards

- Keep changes minimal, focused, and backward compatible with existing node properties.
- Preserve the split between runtime behavior in `nodes/*.js` and editor UI in `nodes/*.html`.
- Do not log secrets, tokens, or full Authorization headers.
- Validate user-provided config and fail with clear actionable errors.
- Prefer small pure helper functions for request building, parsing, and normalization.
- Keep naming consistent with existing node config fields and message outputs.

# Error and Message Contract

- On recoverable API failures, set `msg.statusCode` when available and include a concise `msg.error`.
- Keep successful payloads in `msg.payload` and avoid breaking its shape without migration notes.
- Include enough context in errors to debug endpoint/query issues without exposing credentials.

# Testing and Verification

- Run `npm test` after substantive JS changes.
- Update docs when behavior or node configuration changes.
